0                                   1441      12.              COPY  QLISTMAC
                                    1442             =*******************************************************************
                                    1443             =*                                                                 *
                                    1444             =* These macros are used to update double linked memory lists.     *
                                    1445             =* Serialization is achieved using the PLO instruction. If a       *
                                    1446             =* memory block containing the list head needs to be locked anyway *
                                    1447             =* then the macros in LSTMAC would be better than these.           *
                                    1448             =* Conversely any existing use of LSTMAC macros might be           *
                                    1449             =* converted to this mechanism to avoid using locking.             *
                                    1450             =*                                                                 *
                                    1451             =*******************************************************************
0                                   1453             =*******************************************************************
                                    1454             =*                                                                 *
                                    1455             =* Double linked list head fields                                  *
                                    1456             =*                                                                 *
                                    1457             =*******************************************************************
                                    1458             =         MACRO
                                    1459             =&LAB     QHEAD
                                    1460             =         AIF   ('&LAB' EQ '').ERR
                                    1461             =         DS   0D
                                    1462             =&LAB     DS   0XL(16)              Double linked PLO list
                                    1463             =&LAB.FP  DS    A                   Forward pointer
                                    1464             =&LAB.BP  DS    A                   Backward pointer
                                    1465             =&LAB.SEQ DS    A                   CDS sequence number
                                    1466             =&LAB.CNT DS    A                   Count of items
                                    1467             =         MEXIT
                                    1468             =.ERR     MNOTE 8,'Label (list name) required'
                                    1469             =         MEND
0                                   1471             =*******************************************************************
                                    1472             =*                                                                 *
                                    1473             =* Parameters for the double linked list manipulation routines     *
                                    1474             =* in RESMAN                                                       *
                                    1475             =*                                                                 *
                                    1476             =*******************************************************************

0                                   1511             =         PSET  @QUE,CLEAR=NO
                                    1512             =         LM    R14,R15,&HEAD.SEQ
                                    1513             =         STM   R14,R15,@QUESEQ     Set sequence stuff
                                    1514             =         PMOV  @QUELHD,LA:&HEAD
                                    1515             =         PMOV  @QUEITM,LA:&ITEM
                                    1516             =         LOOP  BEGIN
                                    1517             =         VCALL QUEUE               Add item to end of list
                                    1518             =         UNTIL (RVR,Z),END

0                                   1586      14.              COPY  SLISTMAC
                                    1587             =*******************************************************************
                                    1588             =*                                                                 *
                                    1589             =* Macros for the serialized manipulation of single linked lists   *
                                    1590             =* in memory.  These lists are of the PUSH/POP (LIFO) variety.     *
                                    1591             =* Serialization is achieved using the CDS and CS instructions.    *
                                    1592             =*                                                                 *
                                    1593             =*******************************************************************
0                                   1595             =*******************************************************************
                                    1596             =*                                                                 *
                                    1597             =* Single linked list head fields                                  *
                                    1598             =*                                                                 *
                                    1599             =*******************************************************************
                                    1600             =         MACRO
                                    1601             =&LAB     SHEAD
                                    1602             =         AIF   ('&LAB' EQ '').ERR
                                    1603             =&LAB     DS   0D                   Single linked CDS list
                                    1604             =&LAB.FP  DS    A                   Forward pointer
                                    1605             =&LAB.SEQ DS    A                   CDS sequence number
                                    1606             =         MEXIT
                                    1607             =.ERR     MNOTE 8,'Label (list name) required'
                                    1608             =         MEND
0                                   1610             =*******************************************************************
                                    1611             =*                                                                 *
                                    1612             =* Push an item onto a single linked list                          *
                                    1613             =*                                                                 *
                                    1614             =*******************************************************************
                                    1615             =         MACRO
                                    1616             =&LABEL   SPUSH &HEAD=,&ITEM=
                                    1617             =         LCLC  &X
                                    1618             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    1619             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    1620             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    1621             =         AIF   ('&HEAD' EQ '').ERR1
                                    1622             =         AIF   ('&ITEM' EQ '').ERR2
                                    1624             =         LM    R14,R15,&HEAD       Get fwd ptr and sequence number
                                    1625             =         LA    RVR,&ITEM           Point to new item
                                    1626             =         LOOP  BEGIN
                                    1627             =         LA    RS,1(R15)           Increment sequence
                                    1628             =         MVC   &ITEM.(L'&HEAD.FP),&HEAD.FP Set item fwd ptr
                                    1629             =         CDS   R14,RVR,&HEAD       Add item to list
                                    1630             =         UNTIL (Z),END
                                    1632             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    1633             =.ERR1    MNOTE 8,'Head is a required parameter'
                                    1634             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    1635             =.ERR2    MNOTE 8,'Item is a required parameter'
                                    1636             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    1637             =         MEND  ,
0                                   1639             =*******************************************************************
                                    1640             =*                                                                 *
                                    1641             =* Pop an item from a single linked list. Addr returned in RVR     *

0                                   1642             =* (zero if the list was empty).                                   *
                                    1643             =*                                                                 *
                                    1644             =*******************************************************************
                                    1645             =         MACRO
                                    1646             =&LABEL   SPOP  &HEAD=
                                    1647             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    1648             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    1649             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    1650             =         AIF   ('&HEAD' EQ '').ERR1
                                    1652             =         LM    RVR,RS,&HEAD        Get fwd and sequence number
                                    1653             =         LOOP  BEGIN
                                    1654             =         IF    (RVR,Z),EXIT        None to get
                                    1655             =         LR    R14,RVR             Point to first item
                                    1656             =         L     R14,0(R14)          Get fwd pointer
                                    1657             =         LA    R15,1(RS)           Increment sequence
                                    1658             =         CDS   RVR,R14,&HEAD       Remove item from list
                                    1659             =         UNTIL (Z),END
                                    1661             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    1662             =.ERR1    MNOTE 8,'Head is a required parameter'
                                    1663             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    1664             =         MEND  ,
0                                   1666             =*******************************************************************
                                    1667             =*                                                                 *
                                    1668             =* Get an available item from list (ptr returned in RVR). Memory   *

                                    1670             =*                                                                 *
                                    1671             =*******************************************************************

                                    1680             =         IF    (RVR,Z),BEGIN       empty list

                                    1683             =         END   ,

0                                   1807      18.              COPY  LSTMAC
                                    1808             =         PRINT OFF
                                    1852             =*********************************************************************
                                    1853             =*   Add elements to a list
                                    1854             =*
                                    1855             =*   Input
                                    1856             =*
                                    1857             =* &L  LADD     &HEAD,&FIRST,&FLAST,&FCOUNT,&WR=,&WR2=RAR,&WR3=EPAR
                                    1858             =*     &HEAD    is a pointer the head of the list (defop = LA)
                                    1859             =*     &FIRST   first element to be added to the list
                                    1860             =*     &FLAST   last element to be added (if not specified, assuming
                                    1861             =*              only one)
                                    1862             =*     &FCOUNT  count of elements being added (shouldn't be specified
                                    1863             =*              for only one add)
                                    1864             =*     &WR
                                    1865             =*     &WR2     Registers for scratch
                                    1866             =*     &WR3
                                    1867             =*
                                    1868             =*   Output
                                    1869             =*
                                    1870             =*     No parameter registers are modified
                                    1871             =*
                                    1872             =*********************************************************************
                                    1873             =         PRINT OFF
-
0                                   1968             =*********************************************************************
                                    1969             =*   Remove elements from a list
                                    1970             =*
                                    1971             =*   Input
                                    1972             =*
                                    1973             =* &L  LREM     &HEAD,&FFIRST,&FCOUNT,&LAST=,&WR=,&WR2=RAR,&WR3=EPAR
                                    1974             =*
                                    1975             =*     &HEAD    is a pointer the head of the list (defop = LA)
                                    1976             =*     &FFIRST  first element to be removed from the list (if not
                                    1977             =*              specified then take the first on the list)
                                    1978             =*     &LAST    last element removed (must be specified for multiple
                                    1979             =*              removes, must not be specified for single remove)
                                    1980             =*     &FCOUNT  count of elements to be removed (shouldn't be
                                    1981             =*              specified for single remove)
                                    1982             =*     &WR
                                    1983             =*     &WR2     Registers for scratch
                                    1984             =*     &WR3
                                    1985             =*
                                    1986             =*   Output
                                    1987             =*
                                    1988             =*     RVR      contains the address of the first element on the list
                                    1989             =*     No parameter registers are modified
                                    1990             =*
                                    1991             =*********************************************************************
                                    1992             =         PRINT OFF

0                                   5532             =*****************************************************************
                                    5533             =*
                                    5534             =* Create a general resource item
                                    5535             =*
                                    5536             =*   CALLID is a four byte caller identifier
                                    5537             =*
                                    5538             =*   The resource id is returned in RVR
                                    5539             =*
                                    5540             =*****************************************************************
                                    5541             =         MACRO ,
                                    5542             =&LABEL   GRCRE &CID=
                                    5543             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    5544             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    5545             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    5546             =         AIF   ('&CID' EQ '').ERR
                                    5547             =         PSET  @GRES
                                    5548             =         PMOV  @GRCID,&CID         Set caller id
                                    5549             =         VCALL GRCRE               Create a general resource item
                                    5550             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    5551             =.ERR     MNOTE 8,'CID is a required parameter'
                                    5552             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    5553             =         MEND  ,
0                                   5555             =*****************************************************************

                                    5565             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    5566             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    5567             =         AIF   ('&RID' EQ '').ERR

                                    5578             =* Get a general resource item hold

                                    5582             =*   The resource hold id is returned in RVR

                                    5594             =         AIF   ('&WAIT' NE 'YES').ERR2
                                    5595             =         SET   @GRWAIT
                                    5596             =.EXCL    AIF   ('&EXCL' EQ 'NO').VCALL
                                    5597             =         AIF   ('&EXCL' NE 'YES').ERR3
                                    5598             =         SET   @GREXCL

                                    5602             =         AGO   .EXIT

                                    5604             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    5605             =.ERR3    MNOTE 8,'Valid values for EXCL= are YES or NO'
                                    5606             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    5607             =         MEND  ,

0                                   6912     306.     *
                                    6913     307.     *  This record is used to pass information about IXR files to a
                                    6914     308.     *  system task which will delete them. It is used for regular files
                                    6915     309.     *  and temp files. Temp files are all deleted at detach time.
                                    6916     310.     *  The processing is slightly different in the two cases. FDELB
                                    6917     311.     *  is used as a pointer to an IO buffer which contains the high
                                    6918     312.     *  level IXR for regular files. This same field is used for the
                                    6919     313.     *  block number of the high level IXR for temp files. This is
                                    6920     314.     *  because the count of blocks needs to be obtained from the IXR
                                    6921     315.     *  for regular files before it is passed off to be deleted. We are
                                    6922     316.     *  also trying to avoid any file IO for temp files at detach time.
                                    6923     317.     *  There are also some other minor differences in the two processes.
                                    6924     318.     *
 000000                00000 00015  6925     319.     FDEL     RECORD BEGIN              Temp file delete control block
 000000                             6933  1  320.     FDELFP     DS    A                   Forward pointer
 000004                             6934  1  321.     FDELID     DS    C'FILD'             Block id
 000008                             6935  1  322.     FDELF      DS    A                   FSB
 00000C                             6936  1  323.     FDELB      DS    F                   IXR or block no of file to delete
 000010                             6937  1  324.     FDELC      DS    F                   Block count (non-ixr and hybrid)
 000014 00                          6938  1  325.     FDELFLG    FLAG  ,
 FDELFLG.FDELFN    80 ONES          6942  1  326.                FLAG  FDELFN              Non-IXR file
 FDELFLG.FDELFH    40 ONES          6947  1  327.                FLAG  FDELFH              Hybrid file
 000015                00015 00015  6952     328.              END   ,
